  "text": "About 78 % of the length of second-order axes in adult coffee plants is produced in the warm, rainy season (October to March, active growth), while 22 % is produced during the colddry season (April to September, reduced growth) in South-east Brazil [CITATION_1] , with flowering taking place from September to December and berry harvesting from May to July [CITATION_2] .",
